    "plan_content": "The plan is complete. Here's a summary of what will be built:\n\n## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan\n\n**25 new files**, all inside `extensions/pulseboard/`. Zero existing files touched.\n\n### File structure\n```\nextensions/pulseboard/\n├── openclaw.plugin.json          # Manifest: id \"pulseboard\", channels: [\"pulseboard\"]\n├── package.json                  # @openclaw/pulseboard, no runtime deps, openclaw.channel block\n├── index.ts                      # defineChannelPluginEntry wiring\n├── setup-entry.ts                # defineSetupPluginEntry for setup-only mode\n├── api.ts                        # Public barrel: accounts + setup-surface\n├── channel-config-api.ts         # Exports PulseboardChannelConfigSchema\n└── src/\n    ├── types.ts                  # PulseboardAccountConfig, CoreConfig, InboundMessage, Probe\n    ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod schema → buildChannelConfigSchema\n    ├── config-ui-hints.ts        # UI labels for apiUrl, apiToken, userId, dmPolicy, boardPolicy\n    ├── accounts.ts               # resolveAccount, env vars (PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN, etc.)\n    ├── runtime.ts                # createPluginRuntimeStore singleton\n    ├── runtime-api.ts            # SDK barrel (imports from generic plugin-sdk/* subpaths)\n    ├── normalize.ts              # ~board sigil, target normalization, allowlist matching\n    ├── client.ts                 # Fictional WebSocket client (Node 22 built-in, no npm dep)\n    ├── probe.ts                  # Connect → auth ACK → latency → disconnect\n    ├── send.ts                   # Outbound with activity recording\n    ├── inbound.ts                # Full dispatch: policies, pairing, mention gate, agent route\n    ├── monitor.ts                # runStoppablePassiveMonitor gateway loop\n    ├── setup-core.ts             # ChannelSetupAdapter + config patch helpers\n    ├── setup-surface.ts          # ChannelSetupWizard (token/userId/URL/boards)\n    ├── channel.ts                # createChatChannelPlugin — assembles all adapters\n    ├── channel.test.ts           # textChunkLimit=4000, capabilities, chunker\n    ├── normalize.test.ts         # ~board sigil, prefix stripping, allowlist\n    ├── accounts.test.ts          # configured flag, env var resolution, defaults\n    └── config-schema.test.ts     # Valid parse, dmPolicy=\"open\" guard, uiHints present\n```\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **Board sigil `~`** — `~general` = board (group), `alice` = DM (user ID)\n- **4,000-char chunk limit** — set on `outbound.base.textChunkLimit`\n- **No npm deps** — fictional WebSocket client uses Node 22's built-in `WebSocket`\n- **`runtime-api.ts` barrel** — since no `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` facade can be created without touching core, imports are aggregated from the generic SDK subpaths directly\n- **Capabilities**: `chatTypes: [\"direct\", \"group\"]`, `media: true`, `blockStreaming: true`\n- **Auth**: bearer `apiToken` + `userId` (env: `PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN`, `PULSEBOARD_USER_ID`, `PULSEBOARD_API_URL`)",
